  <summary>5/21/1997--Introduced.
Retirement Savings Commission Act of 1997 - Establishes the Retirement Savings Commission to study and report to the President and Congress on private pension and savings issues and to recommend policies to expand access to and encourage participation in retirement savings vehicles. Requires the Commission to address specified issues and to include in its recommendations measures addressing specified needs of future retirees. Authorizes appropriations.</summary>
